  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WFP for UNHAS activities in West Africa, 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Ebola epidemic in West Africa is the largest outbreak in the history of the disease. WHO estimates that it may take 6-9 months before the outbreak is under control and describes the Ebola outbreak as &quot;a public health emergency of international concern&quot;. WHO issued August 28 an action plan (Ebola Roadmap), which outlines the steps necessary to stop the epidemic within 6-9 months. WHO&apos;s plan had a budget of 490 million US $ and should cover expenses of both national governments, WHO and other UN organizations.
The World Food Programme has issued two separate appeals. One is set to 7.3 million US $ for the establishment and two months of operation of an airlift through the UN Humanitarian Air Service (UNHAS). The air bridge will consist of a 19-seat aircraft and two helicopters. This appeal is, according to WFP 60 per cent funded, but in order to achieve the necessary capacity additional funding is important.</narrative>
  </description>
